# 🃏 Chinchón Multiplayer

Real-time 2-player Chinchón (Spanish card game) built with **FastAPI + WebSockets + vanilla JS**.

## Quick start (local)

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
python server.py
```

Open **http://localhost:8000** in two browser tabs (or two devices on the same network using your IP, e.g. `http://192.168.1.x:8000`).

One player creates a room, shares the 4-letter code, the other joins.

---

## File structure

```
chinchon_mp/
├── server.py          FastAPI + WebSocket server + room management
├── game_logic.py      Pure Python game logic (no dependencies)
├── static/
│   └── index.html     Complete single-file frontend (HTML + CSS + JS)
└── requirements.txt
```

---

## Free cloud deployment

### Railway (recommended — easiest)

1. Push the folder to a GitHub repo
2. Go to [railway.app](https://railway.app) → New Project → Deploy from GitHub
3. Railway auto-detects the Python app. Set the **Start command**:
   ```
   uvicorn server:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT
   ```
4. Done — Railway gives you a public URL instantly.

### Render

1. Push to GitHub
2. [render.com](https://render.com) → New Web Service → Connect repo
3. Build command: `pip install -r requirements.txt`
4. Start command: `uvicorn server:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT`
5. Free tier keeps the server alive as long as someone connects every 15 min.

### Fly.io

```bash
pip install flyctl
flyctl launch           # generates fly.toml
flyctl deploy
```

Add a `Procfile`:
```
web: uvicorn server:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port $PORT
```

---

## Gameplay

| Action | How |
|--------|-----|
| Draw from deck | Click the deck card |
| Take top discard | Click the discard pile card |
| Reorder hand | ← → buttons below each card |
| Discard a card | ↓ button below each card (↓ = normal, ✋ = Stop!, 🏅 = Chinchón!) |
| Declare Win | **✋ Declare Win** button in the header (scores immediately, even incomplete) |
| Reset | 🔄 button in header |

## Scoring

- **Winner of a hand** (stops with 2 valid sets): **−10 points** (bonus)
- **Loser**: pays the sum of their unmatched cards (A=1, 2–7=face value, 10/11/12=10)
- **Chinchón** (7 consecutive same-suit): instant **match win** regardless of scores
- **First to 100 points loses** the match

## Rules

- 40-card Baraja Española: Oros 🪙, Copas 🍷, Espadas ⚔️, Bastos 🏑
- Values: A 2 3 4 5 6 7 10(Sota) 11(Caballo) 12(Rey) — no 8 or 9
- **7 and 10 are consecutive** (key Spanish deck rule)
- Valid **sequence**: 3+ consecutive cards, same suit
- Valid **group**: 3 or 4 cards, same value
- **Winning hand**: two valid sets covering all 7 cards (e.g. 3+4)
